title: fanoutqa: Who are the five most recent mayors of Philadelphia and what are their hometowns? (6ffa8a28719b1246)

chat_history.content: Who are the five most recent mayors of Philadelphia and what are their hometowns?

Here is a list of the five most recent mayors of Philadelphia, along with their hometowns:

1. Jim Kenney (in office since 2016) - Born in Philadelphia, though he grew up in South Philadelphia.
2. Michael Nutter (2008-2016) - Born in Philadelphia.
3. John F. Street (2000-2008) - Born in Northern Liberties, Philadelphia.
4. Ed Rendell (1992-2000) - Born in New York City.
5. Wilson Goode (1984-1992) - Born in North Philadelphia.

Is there anything else you'd like to know about these mayors or the city of Philadelphia?
